    "what_description": "Triplaris triflora is a species of plant in the family Polygonaceae, native to the tropical regions of Central and South America. It is a shrub or small tree that grows up to 10 meters in height, with a grayish-brown bark and a simple or alternate leaf arrangement. The leaves are elliptical in shape, measuring 5-12 cm in length, with a pointed tip and a 2.5-6 cm petiole. The plant produces small, greenish-white flowers in a terminal panicle, 10-30 cm in length, with 4-8 stamens and 2 styles. The fruit is a small, red or purple berry, 4-6 mm in diameter, containing 2-4 seeds.",
