    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Triplaris triflora are quercetin, flavonoids, tannins, phenolic acids, and alkaloids, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. Quercetin, a potent antioxidant and anti-inflammatory flavonoid, contributes to the plant's ability to reduce oxidative stress and inflammation. Flavonoids, such as kaempferol and isorhapontigenin, exhibit anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities, further enhancing the plant's therapeutic potential. Tannins, particularly gallic acid and ellagic acid, possess antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties, while phenolic acids like ferulic acid and sinapic acid display antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities. Alkaloids, including triplarin and triflorin, have been shown to exhibit anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial activities, further supporting the plant's use in traditional medicine.",
